Query: How can customers encrypt the data for security?
combined_response: For at rest encryption, AWS provides tools for creating an encrypted file system using open standard algorithms.
image_and_text_source: for at rest encryption, aws provides tools for creating an encrypted file system using open standard algorithms. for instance, customers can encrypt data stored in amazon s3 and the data stored in amazon elastic block store (amazon ebs) volumes. similarly, aws glue supports data encryption at rest for authoring jobs in aws glue and developing scripts using development endpoints. you can also configure etl jobs and development endpoints to use aws key management service (aws kms). some healthcare customers require the use of aws kms keys. additionally, aws recommends enabling amazon s3 default encryption so that all new objects are encrypted when they are stored in the amazon s3 bucket. aws also recommends using amazon s3 bucket policies to prevent unencrypted objects from being uploaded. for data in transit, all internetwork data in transit supports tls 1.2 encryption.
text_response: For data transmitted between instances during distributed training, inter-container traffic encryption can be enabled.
text_source: for data transmitted between instances during distributed training, inter-container traffic encryption can be enabled.
img_response: Customers can encrypt their data for security by creating an encrypted file system using open standard algorithms.
img_source:
customers can encrypt their data for security by enabling data encryption, both at rest and in transit, as recommended by aws. specific methods mentioned include:

1. creating an encrypted file system using open standard algorithms. 
2. encrypting data stored in amazon s3 and amazon elastic block store (amazon ebs) volumes.
3. enabling data encryption at rest for authoring jobs in aws glue and developing scripts using development endpoints.
4. configuring etl jobs and development endpoints to use aws key management service (aws kms).
5. enabling amazon s3 default encryption so all new objects are encrypted when stored in the s3 bucket.
6. using amazon s3 bucket policies to prevent unencrypted objects from being uploaded.
7. aws states that all internetwork data in transit supports tls 1.2 encryption.
